BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 13 (YONHAP) -- Foreign Minister Han 
Sung-chu talked with his Japanese counterpart Koji Kakizawa, who 
is visiting China, over the telephone Monday and agreed to push 
for gradual sanctions against North Korea. 
  In their telephone conversation lasting 10 minutes from 
12:40 
p. m. (KST), Kakizawa briefed Han on his meeting with Chinese 
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen to discuss the North Korean nuclear 
problem, Ministry spokesman Chang Ki-ho said. 

